{"questionId":"27634","questionHtml":"<p>The derivative of the function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> is given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>.</p>\n<p>The graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> passes through the point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo></math>. Find an expression for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognizing need to integrate&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>u</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mi>u</mi></mfrac><mo>d</mo><mi>u</mi></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; or&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>u</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>correct substitution of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;into equation</p>\n<p>using <strong>their</strong> integrated expression (must involve <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math>)&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mn>8</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>(or equivalent)&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Accept the use of the modulus sign in working and the final answer.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27634","referenceCode":"22N.1.SL.TZ0.5","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"The derivative of the function f is given by f'x=6xx2+1. The graph of y=f(x) passes through the point (1, 5). Find an expression for f(x).","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"5","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.5—Integration introduction, areas between curve and x axis","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.10—Indefinite integration, reverse chain, by substitution"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}